{
  "analysis": "We need to determine the exact tensor layout of the raw checkpoint before finalizing the C model. The file is exactly 124,439,808 float32 values, matching GPT-2 124M if biases are included. I will use compact C probes to print offsets/ranges of likely tensors and test token-embedding dot products against a few known token strings. This will verify the canonical raw layout and guide the implementation.",
  "plan": "Create and compile a small probe program `/tmp/probe.c` that mmaps the checkpoint, defines the standard GPT-2 parameter offsets, and prints counts/offsets plus row norms and dot products for first token rows. Run it to verify that the first tensor is the token embedding matrix. Then use that verified layout to implement `/app/gpt2.c`.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /tmp/probe.c <<'EOF'
#include <stdio.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <sys/mman.h>
#include <sys/stat.h>
#include <fcntl.h>
float W;
float G(int o){return ((float)&W)[o];}
float dot(int r,const char s){
  float d=0;int o=r768;
  for(int i=0;i<768;i++) d+=((float)&W)[o+i];
  return d;
}
int main(){
  int fd=open("/app/gpt2-124M.ckpt",O_RDONLY);
  struct stat st;fstat(fd,&st);
  float P=mmap(0,st.st_size,PROT_READ,MAP_PRIVATE,fd,0);
  W=P;
  long total=st.st_size/4;
  long o=0;
  printf("total %lu\n",total);
  printf("wte %lu %f %f\n",o,G(o),G(o+767));o+=50257768LL;
  printf("wpe %lu %f %f\n",o,G(o),G(o+767));o+=1024768LL;
  long blk=2768+7682304+2304+768768+768+2768+7683072+3072+3072768+768;
  printf("blk %lu\n",blk);
  for(int h=0;h<12;h++){
    printf("h%d ln1g %lu %f ln1b %lu %f\n",h,o,G(o),o+768,G(o+768));o+=2768;
    printf("h%d caw %lu cab %lu cpw %lu cpb %lu\n",h,o,o+7682304,o+7682304+2304,o+7682304+2304+768768);
    o+=7682304+2304+768768+768;
    printf("h%d ln2g %lu ln2b %lu\n",h,o,o+768);o+=2768;
    printf("h%d fcw %lu fcb %lu pw %lu pb %lu\n",h,o,o+7683072,o+7683072+3072,o+7683072+3072+3072768);
    o+=7683072+3072+3072768+768;
  }
  printf("lnfg %lu %f lnfb %lu %f\n",o,G(o),o+768,G(o+768));o+=2768;
  printf("end %lu\n",o);
  for(int r=0;r<5;r++){
    float nr=0;for(int i=0;i<768;i++){float v=G(r768+i);nr+=vv;}
    printf("row %d norm %f dotA %f dotThe %f\n",r,sqrtf(nr),dot(r,"A"),dot(r,"the"));
  }
  return 0;
}
EOF
